    "text": "Home\nReviews\nCES 2023\nGaming\nGear\nEntertainment\nTomorrow\nDeals\nBuying Guides\nVideo\nPodcasts\nLogin\nSign up\nLogin\nReviews\nCES 2023\nGaming\nGear\nEntertainment\nTomorrow\nDeals\nBuying Guides\nVideo\nPodcasts\nASUS' new Xbox controller has a tiny, customizable OLED screen\nThe ROG Raikiri Pro also supports Bluetooth, RF and USB-C.\nBy J. Fingas, 7 hours ago\nEA says 60 percent of corrupted ‘Madden NFL 23’ franchise save files are gone for good\nBy W. Shanklin, a day ago\nThe Latest in Gaming\nRazer's Leviathan V2 Pro PC soundbar can adjust 3D audio based on your head position\nAlong with other gaming gear, Razer revealed a head cushion with near-field 7.1 surround sound and haptic feedback.\nBy K. Holt, 2 hours ago\nThe Razer Edge cloud gaming handheld will be available on January 26th\nThe WiFi model costs $400, and you may have to pay a $200 premium for 5G connectivity.\nBy K. Holt, 3 hours ago\nRazer rounds out its laptop line with the high-spec Blade 16 and Blade 18\nWith massive performance come equally massive price tags.\nBy S. Rutherford, 4 hours ago\nWe have two newsletters, why not sign up for both?\nEngadget Deals\nA weekly roundup of our favorite tech deals\nThe Morning After\nA daily dose of the news you need\nApple PodcastsSpotifyGoogle PlayiHeart Radio\nJust enter your email and we'll take care of the rest:\nSubscribe\nHTC builds a standalone VR / AR headset to rival the Meta Quest Pro\nYou can pre-order the Vive XR Elite today for $1,100.\nBy W. Shanklin, 4 hours ago\nLenovo turns to 'AI' to optimize its 2023 gaming laptops\nMarketing gimmicks are alive and well in the new year.\nBy W. Shanklin, 6 hours ago\nASUS' new Xbox controller has a tiny, customizable OLED screen\nThe ROG Raikiri Pro also supports Bluetooth, RF and USB-C.\nBy J. Fingas, 7 hours ago\nAMD's Ryzen 7000 mobile CPUs feature up to 16 cores and 5.4GHz speeds\nIt's going to be a great year for powerful laptops.\nBy D. Hardawar, 18 hours ago\nAMD's Ryzen 9 7950X3D CPU hits 5.7Ghz, has 144MB of 3D V-Cache\nAMD's 3D cache tech is no longer just an experiment.\nBy D. Hardawar, 18 hours ago\nAMD brings RDNA 3 to laptops with Radeon 7000 GPUs\nAnd there are also a few new RDNA 2 models, as well.\nBy D. Hardawar, 18 hours ago\nSony's Project Leonardo is a controller kit to help people with disabilities play PS5\nProject Leonardo is an accessibility-focused system with no release date.\nBy J. Conditt, 20 hours ago\nNeill Blomkamp's Gran Turismo film certainly looks and sounds like Gran Turismo\nOur first peek at the film shows David Harbour and Orlando Bloom in racing gear.\nBy J. Conditt, 20 hours ago\nEA says 60 percent of corrupted ‘Madden NFL 23’ franchise save files are gone for good\nIf you tried to log into franchise mode during a server problem last week, your data is likely corrupted.\nBy W. Shanklin, a day ago\nMSI is bringing fresh designs and big performance to its Raider and Stealth Studio laptops\nThe Raider is getting a Matrix lightbar while the Stealth Studio features a new magnesium and aluminum chassis.\nBy S. Rutherford, 01.04.2023\nMSI’s new gaming laptops pack NVIDIA GTX 40-series GPUs and redesigned thermals\nPlus what MSI claims is the world's first 4K 144hz mini LED display.\nBy W. Shanklin, 01.04.2023\n90\n6\nNVIDIA RTX 4070 Ti review: 3090 Ti power for $799\nIt’s the first 40-series GPU you may actually afford some day.\nBy D. Hardawar, 01.04.2023\nJBL updates its Quantum lineup of gaming headphones and earbuds\nThe new audio gear works with consoles and PCs.\nBy W. Shanklin, 01.04.2023\nHyperX leans into 3D printing for its next wave of gaming accessories\nThe company is starting with a Cozy Cat keycap and seeing where things go from there.\nBy S. Rutherford, 01.04.2023\nRoland's first gaming product is the Bridge Cast streaming mixer\nExpect submixes, voice effects and a novel way to customize how it looks.\nBy J. Trew, 01.03.2023\nTwitch says it fixed an issue that prevented people from watching streams\nThe problems began at around 1PM ET.\nBy I. Bonifacic, 01.03.2023\nMicrosoft is now the home of the video game industry's largest union\nA supermajority of QA workers at ZeniMax Studios voted to unionize.\nBy J. Conditt, 01.03.2023\nMore Stories\nAbout\nEngadget Masthead\nAbout our Ads\nAdvertise\nFAQ\nRSS Feed\nSections\nReviews\nGear\nGaming\nEntertainment\nTomorrow\nThe Buyers Guide\nVideo\nPodcasts\nDeals\nContribute\nComment Guidelines\nSupport\nInternational\n繁體中文\nSubscribe to our two newsletters:\nEngadget Deals - A weekly roundup of our favorite tech deals\nThe Morning After - A daily dose of the news you need\nSubscribe\nFollow Us\n© 2023 Yahoo. All rights reserved.\nAbout Us\nReprints and Permissions\nSuggestions\nTerms and Privacy Policy\nPrivacy Dashboard\nTrademarks\nAdvertise\nAbout Our Ads",
